The paper discusses Visual Question Answering (VQA) methods, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) communities. The paper also introduces a new dataset and evaluation process, which involves reasoning and generalization, indicating potential relevance to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves text-based evaluation, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
